         <abstract>
            <p>We prove the uniqueness of the quadrature formula with minimal error in the space $\tilde W{}_q^r\lbrack a, b \rbrack, 1 &lt; q &lt; \infty$, of $(b - a)$-periodic differentiable functions among all quadratures with $n$ free nodes $\{x_k\}^n_1$, $a = x_1 &lt; \cdots &lt; x_n &lt; b$, of fixed multiplicities $\{\nu_k\}^n_1$, respectively. As a corollary, we get that the equidistant nodes are optimal in $\tilde W{}_q^r\lbrack a, b \rbrack$ for $1 \leqslant q \leqslant \infty$ if $\nu_1 = \cdots = \nu_n$.</p>
          </abstract>
